# Caesar Cipher Encryption & Decryption Tool

## Project Description
This project was developed as part of the Decode Lab Cybersecurity Internship.
The objective of this project is to implement a basic encryption and decryption technique using the Caesar Cipher algorithm. The program allows users to enter a message and a shift value, then encrypts the message and decrypts it back to its original form.
This project demonstrates the fundamental concepts of cryptography, including encryption, decryption, character manipulation, and secure data handling.

##Project Goal
The main goal of this project is to understand how basic encryption algorithms work by implementing a Caesar Cipher in Java.

##Features
- Encrypt plain text
- Decrypt encrypted text
- User-defined shift value
- Supports uppercase letters
- Supports lowercase letters
- Preserves spaces
- Preserves numbers
- Preserves special characters
- Simple and easy-to-use console interface

